  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RSA_size, RSA_bits</refname>
<refpurpose>get RSA modulus size</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis format="linespecific">#include &lt;openssl/rsa.h&gt;</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">int RSA_size(const RSA *rsa);</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">int RSA_bits(const RSA *rsa);</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.RSA_size.pod:DESCRIPTION"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      RSA_size() returns the RSA modulus size in bytes. It can be used to
      determine how much memory must be allocated for an RSA encrypted
      value.
    </para>
    <para>
      RSA_bits() returns the number of significant bits.
    </para>
    <para>
      <emphasis role="bold">rsa</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">rsa-&gt;n</emphasis> must not be <emphasis role="bold">NULL</emphasis>.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.RSA_size.pod:RETURN_VALUE"><title>RETURN VALUE</title>
    <para>
      The size.
    </para>
  </refsection>
